		<h4>Week 38</h4>
		<p><b>Baby : </b>Uour baby is good to go now! The growth now slows down as development and function of most of the organs in the body is almost complete but thanks to the subcutaneous fat it keeps on growing and the weight gain scale of baby goes on increasing. The muscle mass also increases and  it accounts for almost 25% of babies weight.</p>
		<p>The baby's skin is silky and Pinky. It continues to shed vernix and Lenugo. The sweat glands and oil glands in the skin are functional but the baby doesn't sweat for 3 to 4 weeks after birth because of the immaturity of the body heat regulation system. The lines, loops and whorls are now fully developed on the little finger tips of your child.</p>
		<p>The lungs are still maturing and producing more and more surfactant, a substance that prevents the air sacs in the lungs from sticking to each other once they start to breath.</p>
		<p>Your baby is also swallowing amniotic fluid- some of which winds up in her intestine where it along with other shed cells, bile and waste products turn into your baby's first bowel movement meconium and perhaps your first diaper change.</p>
		<p>Bone continues to grow and harden. the ear lobes now take their shape and all the folds in earlobe are clearly developed. The nails are fully grown and sometimes even extend beyond the fingertips.</p>
		<p>The reproductive organs of boy and girl are fully developed now and the hormones are produced in the body to cope with the stress of labor.</p>
		<p>Most other changes this week are small but important, they continue to add fat and fine-tune her brain and nervous system the way they can deal with all the stimulation that awaits them once they make entrance into the world.</p>

		<p><b>Mom : </b>This last few weeks you might feel better on breathing because your baby now descends into the pelvis and relaxes the pressure put on your internal organs and ribs. There is more comfortable breathing. You may feel heaviness in pelvis because of the descent of the baby. The uterus at sinks into the pelvis. The ligaments  softens and the pelvic cavity widens. In short your body now prepares for the big day.</p>
		<p>By now mothers might have experienced what is Braxton Hicks contraction. It may confuse you that are they the real contractions or the rehearsal ones?! The only difference between the real contraction and Braxton Hicks is that Braxton Hicks contractions are irregular ones and they subside on their own but the labor pain never subsides and interval keeps on decreasing at the intensity of pain keeps on increasing.</p>
		<p>Your baby is tightly held in the uterus and it sleeps more than usual during this time and the movement is decreased compared to previous because the baby is saving energy for the momentous event of arrival into the world.</p>
		<p>While you are waiting for your baby to arrive think of this last week as a dress rehearsal for life with your new arrival. Sleepless nights, a little anxiety and leaky breast. Yes it's true, many pregnant women find that they start leaking Colostrum from breast ,a thin yellowish liquid that's the precursor to breast milk sometime in third trimester. Its full of antibodies that protect your newborn it has more protein and less fat and sugar which is better for baby digestion then the milk.  Not all women experience it though. If not, no need to fret - your breasts are still producing colostrum for your baby when the time comes if you plan to breastfeed.</p>

		<p><b>tips</b></p>
		<p><b>prepare postpartum meals : </b>You should start preparing Indian snacks to stuff your pantry "dabbas" because those first few weeks or even months after the delivery cooking will be the last thing on your mind or your to do list because the baby will keep you so busy that you might end up eating unhealthy packaged foods. start making Indian snacks which are grandmothers and mothers are good at and stuff your pantry.</p>
		<p><b>double check your bag : </b>make sure the items in your hospital bag still fit you. baby cleaning wipes, diapers, 	extra pyjamas, your sanitary kit, multiple pairs of your undergarments this all should be ready in your bag.</p>
		<p><b>go for a walk : </b>daily routine of your walking will help your child to desend.</p>
		<p><b>research distractions : </b>Childbirth education programs generally rely on distraction to teach women to cope with their labour discomfort. Use whatever works best for you. Relaxation, Meditation and Visualisation techniques like imagining that your service. Cervix is opening your child is descending are often useful between contractions and breathing exercise can help during them some women are relaxed and preoccupied by music.</p>
		<p>Keeping your pain in perspective is also key to an easier labour. Staying rested, relaxed and positive will help you stay more comfortable. Tell yourself that the pain of a contraction is actually accomplishing something as each one of us gets you closer to your baby and remember it won't last forever.</p>
		<p><b>wear loose, cool clothing: </b>Perpetually damp this days? Here come those hormones again. Their effects, along with increased blood flow to the skin and increase metabolism during pregnancy can make you sweat more. To stay cool where loose light clothing drinking plenty of water and crack some windows or crank up the AC a sprinkle of talc free powder can also help absorb some moisture plus it can prevent a heat rash that could crop up underneath all that sweat.</p>
		<p><b>do squat exercises : </b>We all have heard tales of women squatting in the field to give birth. Well it turns out there's something to it. Squatting actually speed labour because it increases the pelvic opening providing more room for baby to descend.</p>
		<p><b>try labor inducing foods : </b>Unfortunately, at least as far as medical science is concerned (old wife is a different story), there is no miracle meal that will bring on the labor. In the category of "can't hurt might help" our foods such as brinjal ( eggplant), pineapple, papaya, seasome seeds laddu ,coffee ,chocolates. Whilr there is no proof that any of these are available in using qualities plenty of moms swear by them.</p>

